The paper deals with interpretability in machine learning, specifically in the context of image recognition using convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new mechanism called concept whitening, which modifies the latent space of the network to better align with concepts of interest. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) in the context of image recognition, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category.
